pullRequest.body:
A simplicial object `X` is *n-coskeletal* if the identity natural transformation `X` is a right extension of its
restriction along `(Truncated.inclusion (n := n)).op` recorded by `rightExtensionInclusion X n`. 

Co-Authored-By: [Mario Carneiro](https://github.com/digama0) and [JoÃ«l Riou](https://github.com/joelriou) 

---

This implements a suggestion made in #19057.

The simplicial object `X` is *n-coskeletal* if `rightExtensionInclusion X n` is a right Kan

I would prefer a name like `isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal`.
No problem. I'll change it back. I was trying for greater uniformity but really have no idea what I'm doing..

When we introduce a typeclass (here `IsCoskeletal`) for certain objects (here `SimplicialObject`), it is often convenient to put some definitions or lemmas in the `SimplicialObject` namespace rather than `IsCoskeletal`. One reason is that we can use dot notation, e.g. `X.isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal n`.
(Sorry, my fault here, I think I made bad naming suggestions above.)

```suggestion
instance IsCoskeletal.coskRightExtension.isIso_hom : IsIso (rightExtensionCosk.hom X n) :=
```
(`IsIso` is a Prop, so that this instance is like a lemma, not a def; then we have to use `_` as a separator.)

The name should rather contain `rightExtensionCosk` rather than `coskRightExtension`. Then, better names would be `IsCoskeletal.isIso_rightExtensionCosk_hom` (or `isIso_rightExtensionCosk_hom_of_isCoskeletal`).

As this instance name `Functor.instIsRightKanExtensionObjRanAppRanCounit` was autogenerated by Lean, it would be better to use a syntax like
```lean
  change IsRightKanExtension ...
  infer_instance
```
where in the `change` line, you would put the exact pattern which matches `Functor.instIsRightKanExtensionObjRanAppRanCounit`.
Thanks for the suggestion. I haven't yet mastered the change tactic so it's helpful to get pointers like this.
Though actually here the "change" wasn't needed!

A few of the definitions before this one are unnecessary, a better approach would be:
```lean
-- this instance should be in `SimplicialObject.Basic`
instance : ((cosk n).obj X).IsRightKanExtension ((coskAdj n).counit.app _) := by
  dsimp [cosk, coskAdj]
  rw [ranAdjunction_counit]
  infer_instance

/-- The isomorphism `X â‰… (cosk n).obj X` that exists when `X` is `n`-coskeletal and the
`n`-coskeleton functor exists.-/
noncomputable def isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal : X â‰… (cosk n).obj X :=
  Functor.rightKanExtensionUnique _ (ðŸ™ _) _ ((coskAdj n).counit.app _)

@[simp]
lemma isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal_hom :
    (X.isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal n).hom = (coskAdj n).unit.app X := by
  sorry -- use `hom_ext_of_isRightKanExtension`?
```

Then, using `isRightKanExtension_iff_isIso`, it seems to me it should be easy to show the iff lemma that `X.IsCoskeletal n` iff `IsIso ((coskAdj n).unit.app X)`. It would be nice to add this to this PR.

@joelriou I completed the defs you suggested but had a lot of difficulty, see:

* the four instances `Truncated.isRightKanExtensionCosk` with zero to three primes, all of which Lean couldn't infer at some point 
* `isRightKanExtensionCosk_iff_isIso` vs `isCoskeletal_iff_isIso` (here I'm clearly missing something basic).

I get that the terms I built along the way to the original explicit isomorphism in `isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal` were not of general interest to anyone, but I found that approach to be more straightforward. (I get, though, that this is because I don't know my way around the more general theorems in Mathlib.)

The fact that you had to construct so many variants of the same instance could be a sign that `cosk` should not be defined as `abbrev`, but as a `def`. Let us consider this out of the scope of this PR.
I take this to mean that this is a chore to be explored later in a separate PR. I'll make a note of this.

By making this an instance, it will usable by the right Kan extension API:
```suggestion
instance IsCoskeletal.isRightKanExtension :
```

I was slightly mistaken in my original suggestion, as I had forgotten that `IsRightKanExtension` is a `Prop` (while `IsPointwiseRightKanExtension` contains data):
```suggestion
@[mk_iff]
class IsCoskeletal : Prop where
  isRightKanExtension : IsRightKanExtension X (ðŸ™ ((Truncated.inclusion n).op â‹™ X))

attribute [instance] IsCoskeletal.isRightKanExtension
```

Then, the rest of file could be:
```lean
section

variable [âˆ€ (F : (SimplexCategory.Truncated n)áµ’áµ– â¥¤ C),
    (SimplexCategory.Truncated.inclusion n).op.HasRightKanExtension F]

/-- If `X` is `n`-coskeletal, then `Truncated.rightExtensionInclusion X n` is a terminal object in
the category `RightExtension (Truncated.inclusion n).op (Truncated.inclusion.op â‹™ X)`. -/
noncomputable def IsCoskeletal.isUniversalOfIsRightKanExtension [X.IsCoskeletal n] :
    (rightExtensionInclusion X n).IsUniversal := by
  apply Functor.isUniversalOfIsRightKanExtension

theorem isCoskeletal_iff_isIso : X.IsCoskeletal n â†” IsIso ((coskAdj n).unit.app X) := by
  rw [isCoskeletal_iff]
  exact isRightKanExtension_iff_isIso ((coskAdj n).unit.app X)
    ((coskAdj n).counit.app _) (ðŸ™ _) ((coskAdj n).left_triangle_components X)

instance [X.IsCoskeletal n] : IsIso ((coskAdj n).unit.app X) := by
  rw [â† isCoskeletal_iff_isIso]
  infer_instance

/-- The canonical isomorphism `X â‰… (cosk n).obj X` defined when `X` is coskeletal and the
`n`-coskeleton functor exists.-/
@[simps! hom]
noncomputable def isoCoskOfIsCoskeletal [X.IsCoskeletal n] : X â‰… (cosk n).obj X :=
  asIso ((coskAdj n).unit.app X)

end
```
This is much better. I'm sorry I made this so much harder than it had to be.
It is much easier for me as I authored the Kan extension API for functors!
